how: ALL descriptions are quoted\n\n**12. Content Drift in Shared Skills**\nMinor wording differences in shared skills (reflect, spec have substantive differences beyond Next Step):\n- `reflect` template has more detailed process, new signal type handling for `decisions.md`\n- `spec` template includes step to load all skills at the start\n- These should be unified or explicitly documented as intentional divergence\n\n---\n\n## Summary Table\n\n| Dimension | Critical | Important | Nice-to-Have |\n|-----------|----------|-----------|--------------|\n| YAML frontmatter | — | 3 issues (model, tools, effort) | Quote consistency |\n| Triggers | — | 1 missing, 1 inconsistent format | — |\n| When/Avoid | — | 17 skills missing sections | — |\n| Rules | — | 9 skills missing | Pattern unclear |\n| Deploy/Template parity | 2 skills broken (reflect, spec) | 1 fake skill (skill-creator-workspace) | 6 minor drifts |\n| Description length | — | 2 exceed 200 chars | — |\n| Workflow routing | 9 skills mentioned but missing | — | — |\n| **Total broken skills** | **1** (skill-creator-workspace) | **20+ missing from deploy** | — |\n\n---\n\n## Recommended Actions\n\n**IMMEDIATE**:\n1. Remove skill-creator-workspace from `.claude/skills/` (it's test data)\n2. Add missing `model` and `allowed-tools` to 15 deployed skills\n3. Document intentional deploy/template divergence for reflect/spec OR sync templates to deployed\n\n**SHORT-TERM**:\n1. Add \"Triggers:\" documentation to all skill descriptions (apply-learnings)\n2. Add `## When to Use / ## Avoid If` to 15 skills missing them\n3. Trim gh-cli and session-optimize descriptions to ≤200 chars\n4. Clarify Rules section requirements: which skills need them?\n\n**MEDIUM-TERM**:\n1. Decide: Keep 5 deployed-only skills (agent-browser, bash-defensive-patterns, gh-cli, session-optimize) or deploy the 21 template-only skills\n2. If keeping separate: document the split (deployment vs template project profiles)\n3. Audit workflow.md to match actual 