tate |\n| PostCompact | (none) | 1 | post-compact-restore |\n\n---\n\n### **DETAILED HOOK ANALYSIS BY CATEGORY**\n\n#### **1. PERMISSION DENIED (PermissionDenied event)**\n\n**File:** `/Users/deniskern/Sites/npx-ai-setup/.claude/hooks/permission-denied-log.sh`\n\n**What it does:**\n- Logs permission denials to `.claude/permission-denied.log` with ISO timestamp + full JSON payload\n- Extracts source (permissions.deny, project_settings, user_settings, policy_settings) and emits source-specific hints to stderr\n- No filtering or remediation; purely logging and diagnostic output\n\n**Redundancy check against 2.1.89-2.1.91:**\n- **NOT REDUNDANT.** The hook does NOT use the new `{retry: true}` feature mentioned in your spec. It only logs.\n- The built-in 2.1.90 permission denial handling may have new structured output, but this hook complements it with persistent audit logging.\n- No conflict with built-in features.\n\n**Status:** KEEP. This is a diagnostic/audit hook that doesn't duplicate built-in behavior.\n\n---\n\n#### **2. POST-EDIT LINTING (PostToolUse / Edit|Write)**\n\n**File:** `/Users/deniskern/Sites/npx-ai-setup/.claude/hooks/post-edit-lint.sh`\n\n**What it does:**\n- Runs formatters/linters **after** Edit/Write succeeds\n- Supports project `npm run format` script, ESLint (with --fix), Prettier, and jq JSON validation\n- **CRITICAL:** Actively modifies files via `eslint --fix`, `prettier --write`\n- All output is suppressed to stderr (hidden from Claude) to prevent fix-loop prompts\n\n**Redundancy check against 2.1.89-2.1.91:**\n- **COMPATIBILITY CONCERN (2.1.90 fix).** The hook DOES modify files in-place via `eslint --fix` and `prettier --write`. Before Claude Code 2.1.90, this would have failed silently (tool output not captured). The 2.1.90 fix added proper hook-output file handling.\n- **This hook still works** because it doesn't rely on the output file feature; it modifies disk directly.\n- However, the pattern \"run linter after each edit\" is now more robust with the new hook output file feature (50K char limit). If output was intended to be logged, the new feature would help.\n- **Recommendation:** No change needed unless you want to log formatter output. Current implementation is safe.\n\n**Status:** KEEP AS-IS. Works correctly; no redundancy with built-in features.\n\n---\n\n#### **3. CIRCUIT BREAKER (PreToolUse / Edit|Write)**\n\n**File:** `/Users/deniskern/Sites/npx-ai-setup/.claude/hooks/protect-and-breaker.sh`\n\n**What it does:**\n- **Protected file check:** Blocks edits to `.env`, lock files, `.git/`, assets/ (in Vite projects)\n- **Circuit breaker:** Detects edit loops on the same file\n  - Warns at 5 edits/10min, blocks at 8 edits/10min\n  - Raises thresholds to 12/20 (or 25/40 for 2+ active specs) when specs are in-progress\n  - Resets on `UserPromptSubmit` via context-freshness.sh\n  - Stores log in `/tmp/claude-cb-${PROJ_HASH}.log` using tab-delimited file paths\n\n**Redundancy check against 2.1.89-2.1.91:**\n- **NEW BUILT-IN in 2.1.89:** \"autocompact thrash loop\" fix detects and prevents edit/retry loops that trigger compaction\n- **KEY DIFFERENCE:** The built-in 2.1.89 feature targets **compaction-triggering loops**, while your circuit-breaker targets **any edit loop on same file**\n  - Overlaps in scope but different trigger mechanisms\n  - Your hook is faster (local counters) and more configurable (spec-aware thresholds)\n  - Built-in prevents thrashing the compactor; your hook prevents manual debugging loops\n- **NOT REDUNDANT.** They address complementary concerns.\n- **Note:** The hook uses tab-delimited log format with space-separated fallback in templates/circuit-breaker.sh (`$2==f` vs `NF>=2 && $2==f`). Current implementation is more robust.\n\n**Status:** KEEP. Complements 2.1.89 thrash loop protection. No conflicts.\n\n---\n\n#### **4. CONTEXT MONITORING (PostToolUse / Edit|Write|NotebookEdit)**\n\n**File:** `/Users/deniskern/Sites/npx-ai-setup/.claude/hooks/context-monitor.sh`\n\n**Wha